 applied for type II solar\nradio bursts. The radiation pattern in both cases is quadrupolar, and we show\nthat emission from density clumps may efficiently contribute to the visibility\nof harmonic radio emission.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 23 Dec 2020 16:26:50 GMT"}],"update_date":"2021-02-24"}
