issolves. The second\nmigration mode occurs when the gap is deep so that the planet's eccentricity\ngrows to a value ~0.2 due to inefficient eccentricity damping by corotation\nresonances. This second, faster migration mode appears to be typical of 2D\nmodels in discs with slower damping of temperature's perturbations.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 23 Dec 2020 19:36:21 GMT"}],"update_date":"2021-03-03"}
